Uses some code from the Emacs Wave client

http://code.google.com/p/wave-client-for-emacs/

and some ideas from Rudel

http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/Rudel
http://rudel.bzr.sf.net/bzr/rudel/branches/etherpad/files/

to connect to the experimental Etherpad Lite.

Note that you need to make the following changes to recent
versions of Etherpad Lite to enable websockets:

https://github.com/Pita/etherpad-lite/blob/master/node/server.js#L422

    // io.set('transports', ['xhr-polling']);
    io.set('transports', ['websocket']);

and then change the version number of socket.io in 

  https://github.com/Pita/etherpad-lite/blob/master/package.json#L13 

to 0.8.6, and execute bin/installDeps.sh 